            Just send this link to your users, and they will be notified whenever you are online automatically!
        </p>

        <div class="row">
            <div class="col-lg-8 col-xl-7 table-responsive">
                <table class="table table-sm">
                    <thead>
                        <tr>
                            <th scope="col">Your site</th>
                            <th scope="col">Your link</th>
                        </tr>
                    </thead>
                    <tr>
                        <td>Twitch</td>
                        <td class="text-nowrap overflow-auto mono">https://siren.chat/tw/<strong><em>YOUR_TWITCH_CHANNEL</em></strong></td>
                    </tr>
                    <tr>
                        <td>Chaturbate</td>
                        <td class="text-nowrap overflow-auto mono">https://siren.chat/cb/<strong><em>YOUR_USERNAME</em></strong></td>
                    </tr>
                    <tr>
                        <td>Stripchat</td>
                        <td class="text-nowrap overflow-auto mono">https://siren.chat/sc/<strong><em>YOUR_USERNAME</em></strong></td>
                    </tr>
                    <tr>
                        <td>BongaCams</td>
                        <td class="text-nowrap overflow-auto mono">https://siren.chat/bc/<strong><em>YOUR_USERNAME</em></strong></td>
                    </tr>
                    <tr>
                        <td>LiveJasmin</td>
                        <td class="text-nowrap overflow-auto mono">https://siren.chat/lj/<strong><em>YOUR_USERNAME</em></strong></td>
                    </tr>
                    <tr>
                        <td>CamSoda</td>
                        <td class="text-nowrap overflow-auto mono">https://siren.chat/cs/<strong><em>YOUR_USERNAME</em></strong></td>
                    </tr>
                    <tr>
                        <td>Flirt4Free</td>
                        <td class="text-nowrap overflow-auto mono">https://siren.chat/f4f/<strong><em>YOUR_USERNAME</em></strong></td>
                    </tr>
                    <tr>
                        <td>Streamate</td>
                        <td class="text-nowrap overflow-auto mono">https://siren.chat/sm/<strong><em>YOUR_USERNAME</em></strong></td>
                    </tr>
                </table>
            </div>
        </div>

        <p class="mt-3">
            Substitute <em><strong>YOUR_USERNAME</strong></em> with your actual login username.
        </p>

        <p class="p-3 mb-3 bg-warning">
            For BongaCams models. Please don't use your display name or real name. Use the username you log in with!
        </p>

        <p>
            First of all we need to say, this bot has nothing to do with you personal Telegram account.
            You don't need to have Telegram to use it.
            This is simple. You provide a link to the user.
            The user clicks it and receive notifications whenever you are online.
            The only thing you need to do is to start broadcasting.
            Our bot checks who is online and sends notifications automatically.
        </p>

        <p>
            Add the subscription link to your profile page on Chaturbate, Stripchat and BongaCams.
            You can set up an icon in Chaturbate via our <a href="/chic">Chaturbate icons constructor</a>.
            Also share this link on Twitter, Instagram or other social media.
        </p>

        <p>Recommended text: "Get a notification in Telegram whenever I'm online <em><strong>YOUR LINK</strong></em>".</p>
        <p>These bots talk in English. For bots in other languages change the language at the bottom of the page.</p>
        <p>Write to <a href="mailto:siren.chat@gmail.com">siren.chat@gmail.com</a> in case of any questions.</p>

        <h3 id="channel">Automatic notifications in your Telegram channel or group</h3>
        <p>
            You can automatically notify your users whenever you are online in your Telegram channel or group!
        </p>

        <h4>Step 1</h4>
        <p>
            Add our bot to your Telegram group or channel.
            These bots talk in English.
            For bots in other languages change the language at the bottom of the page.
        </p>

        <div class="row">
            <div class="col-lg-8 col-xl-7 table-responsive">
                <table class="table table-sm">
                    <thead>
                        <tr>
                            <th scope="col">Your site</th>
                            <th scope="col">Bot</th>
                        </tr>
                    </thead>
                    <tr>
                        <td>Twitch</td>
                        <td class="text-nowrap overflow-auto mono">TwitchSirenBot</td>
                    </tr>
                    <tr>
                        <td>Chaturbate</td>
                        <td class="text-nowrap overflow-auto mono">ChaturbateAlarmBot</td>
                    </tr>
                    <tr>
                        <td>Stripchat</td>
                        <td class="text-nowrap overflow-auto mono">StripchatOnlineBot</td>
                    </tr>
                    <tr>
                        <td>BongaCams</td>
                        <td class="text-nowrap overflow-auto mono">BongaCamsOnlineBot</td>
                    </tr>
                    <tr>
                        <td>LiveJasmin</td>
                        <td class="text-nowrap overflow-auto mono">LiveJasminSirenBot</td>
                    </tr>
                    <tr>
                        <td>CamSoda</td>
                        <td class="text-nowrap overflow-auto mono">CamSodaSirenBot</td>
                    </tr>
                    <tr>
                        <td>Flirt4Free</td>
                        <td class="text-nowrap overflow-auto mono">Flirt4FreeSirenBot</td>
                    </tr>
                    <tr>
                        <td>Streamate</td>
                        <td class="text-nowrap overflow-auto mono">StreamateSirenBot</td>
                    </tr>
                </table>
            </div>
        </div>

        <p>
            If you add a bot to a channel, not a group, ensure it is admin, and it has a permission to read and write messages.
        </p>

        <h4>Step 2</h4>
        <p>
            Enter the following command.
        </p>

        <div class="row">
            <div class="col-lg-8 col-xl-7 table-responsive">
                <table class="table table-sm">
                    <thead>
                        <tr>
                            <th scope="col">Your site</th>
                            <th scope="col">Command</th>
                        </tr>
                    </thead>
                    <tr>
                        <td>Twitch</td>
                        <td class="text-nowrap overflow-auto mono">add@TwitchSirenBot <strong><em>YOUR_TWITCH_CHANNEL</em></strong></td>
                    </tr>
                    <tr>
                        <td>Chaturbate</td>
                        <td class="text-nowrap overflow-auto mono">add@ChaturbateAlarmBot <strong><em>YOUR_USERNAME</em></strong></td>
                    </tr>
                    <tr>
                        <td>Stripchat</td>
                        <td class="text-nowrap overflow-auto mono">add@StripchatOnlineBot <strong><em>YOUR_USERNAME</em></strong></td>
                    </tr>
                    <tr>
                        <td>BongaCams</td>
                        <td class="text-nowrap overflow-auto mono">add@BongaCamsOnlineBot <strong><em>YOUR_USERNAME</em></strong></td>
                    </tr>
                    <tr>
                        <td>LiveJasmin</td>
                        <td class="text-nowrap overflow-auto mono">add@LiveJasminSirenBot <strong><em>YOUR_USERNAME</em></strong></td>
                    </tr>
                    <tr>
                        <td>CamSoda</td>
                        <td class="text-nowrap overflow-auto mono">add@CamSodaSirenBot <strong><em>YOUR_USERNAME</em></strong></td>
                    </tr>
                    <tr>
                        <td>Flirt4Free</td>
                        <td class="text-nowrap overflow-auto mono">add@Flirt4FreeSirenBot <strong><em>YOUR_USERNAME</em></strong></td>
                    </tr>
                    <tr>
                        <td>Streamate</td>
                        <td class="text-nowrap overflow-auto mono">add@StreamateSirenBot <strong><em>YOUR_USERNAME</em></strong></td>
                    </tr>
                </table>
            </div>
        </div>
        <p>You can remove this command after bot is set up.</p>

        <h4>Step 3 (optional)</h4>
        <p>
            We also send offline notifications by default. You can disable them by entering this command.
        </p>
        <div class="row">
            <div class="col-lg-9 col-xl-8 table-responsive">
                <table class="table table-sm">
                    <thead>
                        <tr>
                            <th scope="col">Your site</th>
                            <th scope="col">Command</th>
                        </tr>
                    </thead>
                    <tr>
                        <td>Twitch</td>
                        <td class="text-nowrap overflow-auto mono">disable_offline_notifications@TwitchSirenBot</td>
                    </tr>
                    <tr>
                        <td>Chaturbate</td>
                        <td class="text-nowrap overflow-auto mono">disable_offline_notifications@ChaturbateAlarmBot</td>
                    </tr>
                    <tr>
                        <td>Stripchat</td>
                        <td class="text-nowrap overflow-auto mono">disable_offline_notifications@StripchatOnlineBot</td>
                    </tr>
                    <tr>
                        <td>BongaCams</td>
                        <td class="text-nowrap overflow-auto mono">disable_offline_notifications@BongaCamsOnlineBot</td>
                    </tr>
                    <tr>
                        <td>LiveJasmin</td>
                        <td class="text-nowrap overflow-auto mono">disable_offline_notifications@LiveJasminSirenBot</td>
                    </tr>
                    <tr>
                        <td>CamSoda</td>
                        <td class="text-nowrap overflow-auto mono">disable_offline_notifications@CamSodaSirenBot</td>
                    </tr>
                    <tr>
                        <td>Flirt4Free</td>
                        <td class="text-nowrap overflow-auto mono">disable_offline_notifications@Flirt4FreeSirenBot</td>
                    </tr>
                    <tr>
                        <td>Streamate</td>
                        <td class="text-nowrap overflow-auto mono">disable_offline_notifications@StreamateSirenBot</td>
                    </tr>
                </table>
            </div>
        </div>
        <p>
            You can remove this command after bot is set up.
            To enable offline notifications again just replace <span class="mono">disable</span> by <span class="mono">enable</span>.
        </p>

        <h4>Step 4 (optional)</h4>
        <p>
            You may want to disable screenshots sending as well. You can disable them by entering this command.
        </p>
        <div class="row">
            <div class="col-lg-9 col-xl-8 table-responsive">
                <table class="table table-sm">
                    <thead>
                        <tr>
                            <th scope="col">Your site</th>
                            <th scope="col">Command</th>
                        </tr>
                    </thead>
                    <tr>
                        <td>Twitch</td>
                        <td class="text-nowrap overflow-auto mono">disable_images@TwitchSirenBot</td>
                    </tr>
                    <tr>
                        <td>Chaturbate</td>
                        <td class="text-nowrap overflow-auto mono">disable_images@ChaturbateAlarmBot</td>
                    </tr>
                    <tr>
                        <td>Stripchat</td>
